===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} — a sharp peg. Same as {{zh-l|*弋}} and {{zh-l|*尗}}. The sense "talent" is via an early phonetic loan. See also the top component of {{zh-l|*𢦏}}.

{{w|Xu Shen|Xu Shen}} erroneously analyzed this character as a sprout growing from the ground.

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*tsa ~ za||child, offspring, relatives; to come forth (as child at birth); to love; loving}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). "Birth" and "natural characteristic / endowments" are semantically connected, compare {{och-l|生|live, give birth}} and its derivative {{och-l|性|nature; character; personality; quality}} & {{och-l|姓|family name}}. Cognate with {{och-l|子|son}}.

Derivatives: {{och-l|材|material; timber}}, {{och-l|財|riches; property; money}}, and {{och-l|存|to exist}}.

